Objective:
- Add Google Docs ingestion (from Drive folders) to create/update spreadsheets as base language sources. Docs are one-way inputs (never synced back), used once unless doc mtime is newer than the derived spreadsheet; updates only apply to base-language content + new keys.

Constraints / guardrails:
- Respect existing folder scanning and flatten/per-spreadsheet modes.
- Derive locale from filename ([project]_[lang]) with localeNormalizer validation; require explicit sourceLocale fallback.
- Keys/variables must be deterministic and meaningful from doc content; avoid churn across re-ingests.
- Spreadsheet remains source of truth after creation; Doc only used as feeder/refresh when doc mtime > sheet mtime and update is safe.
- Auto-translate behavior stays in sheets (GOOGLETRANSLATE); Docs not used for translation automation.

Proposed plan (phased):
- Discovery & config
  - Add options: scanForDocs (default false), docNameFilter (RegExp), docLanguageFromName (bool), docSourceLocale (fallback), docExportMime (markdown preferred), docIds (explicit), docKeyStrategy (heading|marker|numbered), docUpdateMode (create-only|refresh-if-newer).
  - Extend driveFolderScanner to pick up Docs MIME with folderPath, modifiedTime, inferred locale.
  - Extend manifest to record docs (id, name, folderPath, modifiedTime, sourceLocale, exportFormat, generatedFromDoc: true).
- Fetch & parse
  - Implement doc exporter via Drive API export (markdown/text); enforce concurrency limits and respectful backoff.
  - Implement doc parser → TranslationData shape:
    - Key derivation: prefer explicit markers [[key:path.to.string]], else slugified headings + stable ordinal fallback.
    - Capture base locale from doc naming or config; ignore other locales in doc (single-locale source).
    - Preserve structure deterministically to avoid key churn.
- Integrate with sheet pipeline
  - Convert parsed doc to languageData.json-compatible structure.
  - For create: generate new spreadsheet via existing spreadsheetCreator with doc-derived base locale and keys.
  - For refresh: if doc modifiedTime > spreadsheet modifiedTime and docUpdateMode allows, update base-language sheet content and add new keys; do not touch non-base locales except to re-seed missing cells via autoTranslate rules.
  - Ensure one-way flow: never write back to Docs; mark manifest with lastDocIngest timestamp.
- Sync & collision policy
  - Collision: spreadsheet wins for existing keys unless doc is newer AND docUpdateMode=refresh; log skips.
  - New keys from doc always added; base-language values overwritten only when doc is newer.
  - Respect cleanPush only for initial create; avoid wiping user edits in other locales.
- Testing
  - driveFolderScanner: docs MIME discovery, locale inference, filters, recursion.
  - doc parser: markers vs headings, stable key generation, whitespace/format edge cases.
  - doc export: mocks of Drive export; concurrency/backoff.
  - integration: doc → spreadsheet create; doc newer → refresh base values + new keys; doc older → no-op.
  - manifest: includes docs metadata and generatedFromDoc flag.
- Types & safety
  - Add doc types to public API (discriminated union for manifest entries).
  - Strong types for config and parser output; guard invalid locales.
  - Graceful error handling: skip failing docs, continue others; structured warnings.
- Documentation
  - Usage guide: naming convention, one-way nature, update rules, options, limitations (no doc back-sync, translation still in sheets).
  - Examples for filename-based locale inference and marker-based keys.

Acceptance criteria:
- Docs in Drive folders can be discovered (opt-in), exported, parsed into deterministic keys, and used to create a spreadsheet with base locale set from doc.
- When a source doc is modified later, a refresh updates base-language values and adds new keys if doc mtime is newer; non-base locales remain intact except missing cells can still auto-translate.
- Manifest records docs and ingest metadata; docs are never treated as writable targets.
- Tests cover discovery, parsing, create+refresh flows, collision policy, and manifest updates.
- No regressions to existing spreadsheet/image flows; type-safe public API extensions.
